                    "name": "Breath Weapon",
                    "type": "stat_block_section",
                    "text": "The chimera breathes a cone or line that deals 9d6 damage to all creatures in the area (DC 26 basic save of a type indicated below). The color of the chimera\u2019s dragon head determines the area of the Breath Weapon, the type of damage it deals, and the type of save to avoid it. The chimera can\u2019t use Breath Weapon again for 1d4 rounds.<br/><ul><li><b>Black</b> 60-foot line of acid (Reflex)</li><li><b>Blue</b> 60-foot line of electricity (Reflex)</li><li><b>Green</b> 30-foot cone of poison (Fortitude)</li><li><b>Red</b> 30-foot cone of fire (Reflex)</li><li><b>White</b> 30-foot cone of cold (Reflex)</li></ul>",
